  "prompt": "We are inviting my parents in uk. Is there going to be a problem with their application because we live in 1 bedroom flat?",
  "response": "The success of a visitor visa application depends on several factors, and living in a 1-bedroom flat doesn't automatically disqualify your parents from getting a visa. However, here are some considerations:\n\n1. Accommodation\n- You'll need to demonstrate that there's adequate space and arrangements for their stay\n- Provide details about sleeping arrangements\n- Having a sofa bed or pull-out bed can be helpful\n- Show proof that the accommodation can comfortably host guests\n\n2. Financial Requirements\n- Prove you can support them during their visit\n- Show you have sufficient funds to cover their stay\n- Provide evidence of stable income and accommodation\n\n3. Other Important Factors\n- Strong ties to their home country\n- Clear travel history\n- Purpose of visit\n- Financial stability\n- Intention to return after visit\n\nRecommendations:\n- Be honest in the application\n- Provide clear documentation\n- Explain sleeping arrangements\n- Show financial capability\n- Include details about planned activities\n\nThe key is to demonstrate that their visit is genuine and they have no intention of staying permanently.\n\nConsider consulting an immigration lawyer or advisor for personalized guidance specific to your situation.",
